Some asked him to delineate between the religion of positivism and the science of positivism. Eventually, he revised Positive Philosophy, renaming the science of positivism by taking the Latin root Socius (meaning group or relationship) and coupling it with the Greek work logos (meaning knowledge or study). Hence, sociology.
